1 l. Nitrosamine and nitrosamine releasers, including diethanolamine and
2 triethanolamine.
3 …."
4 SECTION 2. G.S. 106-132 reads as rewritten:
5 "§ 106-132. Additives, etc., deemed unsafe.
6 Any added poisonous or added deleterious substance, any food additive, any pesticide
7 chemical in or on a raw agricultural commodity or any color additive, shall with respect to any
8 particular use or intended use be deemed unsafe for the purpose of application of
9 G.S. 106-129(1), paragraphs b and g and 106-129(4) with respect to any food, 106-133(1) with
10 respect to any drug or device, or 106-136(1) and (5) 106-136(1), (5), and (6) with respect to any
11 cosmetic, unless there is in effect a regulation pursuant to G.S. 106-139 of this Article limiting
12 the quantity of substance, and the use or intended use of such substance conforms to the terms
13 prescribed by such regulation. While such regulations relating to such substance are in effect, a
14 food, drug, or cosmetic shall not, by reason of bearing or containing such substance in accordance
15 with the regulations be considered adulterated within the meaning of G.S. 106-129(1)a,
16 106-133(1) and 106-136(1)."
17 SECTION 3. G.S. 106-136 reads as rewritten:
18 "§ 106-136. Cosmetics deemed adulterated.
19 A cosmetic shall be deemed to be adulterated:
20 …
21 (6) If it contains a restricted substance as an intentionally added chemical in any
22 amount, including as a nonfunctional by-product or a nonfunctional
23 contaminant above the practical quantification limit. The practical
24 quantification limit must be based on scientifically defensible, standard
25 analytical methods. The practical quantification limit for a given restricted
26 substance may be different depending on the analytical method used."
27 SECTION 4. Article 12 of Chapter 120 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
28 a new section to read:
29 "§ 106-141.2. Certificate of compliance for cosmetic products.
30 (a) If the Board of Agriculture has reason to believe that a cosmetic product contains a
31 restricted substance as an intentionally added chemical and is being offered for sale in violation
32 of this article, the Board may issue a notice to the manufacturer of the cosmetic product to provide
33 the Board with a certificate of compliance attesting that the cosmetic product does not contain a
34 restricted substance as an intentionally added chemical no later than 30 days after the date of the
35 notice.
36 (b) A manufacturer that does not provide a certificate of compliance shall notify persons
37 that sell that cosmetic product in this State that the sale of that cosmetic product is prohibited in
38 this State and provide the Board of Agriculture with a list of the names and addresses of those
39 notified no later than 30 days after the date of the notice."
40 SECTION 5. This act becomes effective January 1, 2026.
